## ğŸ“– 4. Networking Commands Cheat Sheet  

Networking commands are essential for troubleshooting, monitoring, and managing network configurations.  

### ğŸ” **Essential Commands & Usage**  

#### ğŸ–¥ï¸ **1. Check Connectivity (Ping)**
```sh
ping google.com
```
âœ… Tests if a host is reachable over the network.  

#### ğŸŒ **2. Trace Packet Route (Traceroute)**
```sh
traceroute google.com   # Linux/macOS
tracert google.com      # Windows
```
âœ… Shows the path packets take to reach a destination.  

#### ğŸ“¡ **3. View Network Connections (Netstat)**
```sh
netstat -tuln
```
âœ… Displays active connections, listening ports, and routing tables.  

#### ğŸ”— **4. Perform HTTP Requests (Curl)**
```sh
curl -I https://google.com
```
âœ… Fetches HTTP headers for troubleshooting web services.  

#### ğŸŒ **5. Perform DNS Lookup (Dig & Nslookup)**
```sh
dig google.com
nslookup google.com
```
âœ… Resolves domain names to IP addresses.  

